{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Email adapter implemented with template rendering, recipient resolution, and pluggable transport","detail":"Three-layer design: (1) RecipientResolver function type resolves identifiers to email addresses — default treats '@'-containing strings as emails, custom resolvers can look up user IDs. (2) Template rendering via a TEMPLATES record keyed by NotificationType — each template produces subject, HTML, and plain-text output with HTML escaping for XSS safety. (3) EmailTransport interface abstracts delivery — InMemoryTransport for dev/test, swap for real providers. This keeps the adapter testable and extensible without changing the NotificationAdapter contract.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/adapters/email.adapter.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN10WRNNWE2YXM6DYKQEZVBH","timestamp":"2026-03-31T04:02:12.277Z"}
